    "keywords" -> {
     "fermionic quantum computation", "fermionic Gaussian state"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "WickLindbladSolve[ham, jmp, in, {ti, tf, dt}] solves the Lindblad \
equation associated with the Hamiltonia ham and a set of quantum jump \
operators jmp for the initial condition in, and returns the single-particle \
Green's function matrices at times from ti to tf at step dt. \
WickLindbladSolve[spec, ..., {{t1, t2, ..., tn}}] calculates the Green's \
function matrix at times {t1, t2, ..., tn}. Note the double curly bracket.", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "WickLindbladSolve", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
